Ayala Land, Digital, Petron, Globe: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-29T00:38:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/ayala-land-digital-petron-globe-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 1 percent to
4,278.83.  Ayala Land Inc. (ALI)  : The largest developer said a unit
was permitted by the Energy Regulatory Commission to sell
electricity to end-users within the Ayala Group. The stock fell
1.6 percent to 16.40 pesos.  Petron Corp. (PCOR)  : The government may extend the fuel
subsidy to public transport groups “for another month or two”
and the economic team has “lined up a number of
recommendations” to shield the public from rising costs,
President  Benigno Aquino ’s spokesman Edwin Lacierda said. The
government may spend “more than a billion” pesos for the fuel
subsidy, he said. Petron, the nation’s biggest oil refiner, rose
0.3 percent to 13.82 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
